<div id="outline-container-xlibre-prereqs" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="xlibre-prereqs">Prerequisites</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-xlibre-prereqs">
<p>
The XLibre X server exists in the binary repositories since
FreeBSD 15.0. So this version of OS or higher is necessary.
</p>

<p>
It is worth to create a ZFS boot environment with <code>beadm</code> before:
</p>
<pre class="example">
doas beadm create 15.0-before-xlibre
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-test" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="test">How to switch</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-test">
<pre class="example">
doas pkg install xlibre
</pre>

<p>
In my case I need some additional drivers for Wacom and for my Intel
integrated videocard, so I used this command:
</p>
<pre class="example">
doas pkg install xlibre xlibre-xf86-input-evdev xlibre-xf86-input-wacom xlibre-xf86-video-intel
</pre>

<p>
During the installation the Xorg will be replaced by XLibre. No any
changes in the configuration files are required:
</p>
<pre class="example">
New packages to be INSTALLED:
        basu: 0.2.1 [FreeBSD-ports]
        seatd: 0.9.2 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre: 0.1 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-drivers: 1.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-server: 25.1.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-input-evdev: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-input-keyboard: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-input-libinput: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-input-mouse: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-input-wacom: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-video-intel: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-video-scfb: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]
        xlibre-xf86-video-vesa: 25.0.0 [FreeBSD-ports]

Installed packages to be REMOVED:
        xf86-input-evdev: 2.10.6_8
        xf86-input-keyboard: 1.9.0_6
        xf86-input-libinput: 1.3.0_1
        xf86-input-mouse: 1.9.3_5
        xf86-video-scfb: 0.0.7_2
        xf86-video-vesa: 2.5.0_3
        xorg: 7.7_3
        xorg-drivers: 7.7_7
        xorg-server: 21.1.20,1

Number of packages to be removed: 9
Number of packages to be installed: 13
</pre>

<p>
After that the "soft restart" is required to restart X server,
launched by xdm:
</p>
<pre class="example">
doas reboot -r
</pre>

<p>
Done!
</p>
<pre class="example">
drag0n@drag0n-laptop:~ $ doas X -version

XLibre X Server 1.25.1
X Protocol Version 11, Revision 0
Current Operating System: FreeBSD drag0n-laptop.lair.internal 15.0-RELEASE FreeBSD 15.0-RELEASE releng/15.0-n280995-7aedc8de6446 GENERIC amd64
Current version of pixman: 0.46.2
</pre>

<p>
All things works out of the box. My recipes, described in my previous
blog post: <a href="https://eugene-andrienko.com/it/2025/07/24/x11-configuration-simple.html">"How to configure X11 in a simple way"</a> — works too.
</p>


